test-set.name: app-spec-examples
test-set.description: Tests the example code in the F+O 3.1 specification

test-case.name: fo-test-fn-string-007
test-case.test:
let $para :=
<para>In a hole in the ground there lived a <term author="Tolkien">hobbit</term>.</para>
return
string($para)

result.assert-deep-eq: "In a hole in the ground there lived a hobbit."

test-case.name: fo-test-fn-data-004
test-case.test:
let $para :=
<para>In a hole in the ground there lived a <term author="Tolkien">hobbit</term>.</para>
return
data($para)

result.assert-deep-eq: xs:untypedAtomic("In a hole in the ground there lived a hobbit.")

test-case.name: fo-test-fn-data-005
test-case.test:
let $para :=
<para>In a hole in the ground there lived a <term author="Tolkien">hobbit</term>.</para>
return
data($para/term/@author)

test-case.name: fo-test-fn-concat-002
test-case.test: fn:concat('Thy ', (), 'old ', "groans", "", ' ring', ' yet', ' in', ' my', ' ancient',' ears.')

result.assert-deep-eq: "Thy old groans ring yet in my ancient ears."
